he heat. Besides, nobody wants to spend 20 minutes on a hairstyle that will deflate 10 minutes after you step out in the sun. <p> </p>

We’ve created a selection of easy summer hairstyles that will last all day for when the weather heats up in the coming months.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-070e" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-jNHqnW kXSKNz pf-24_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-cqJhZP gRKDwp"><div class="sc-efQSVx kdrjec pf-25_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eySxxw fIKYYX pf-26_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-27_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-29_">1. The simple ballerina bun </span></h3></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eySxxw fIKYYX pf-30_"><div title="Cute and Easy Summer Hairstyles" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-TBWPX ebxtzr pf-31_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/the-simple-ballerina-bun-1666017461410_1200x.jpg?v=1666017461" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/the-simple-ballerina-bun-1666017461410.jpg?v=1666017461 1536w" width="927" height="926" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" alt="Easy Summer Hairstyles" title="Cute and Easy Summer Hairstyles"/></div></div></div></div><div class="sc-efQSVx kdrjec pf-32_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eySxxw fIKYYX pf-33_"><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-34_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-36_">The obvious choice for the steamy summer months is a simple <a href="https://www.cliphair.co.uk/blogs/hair-blog/hairgoals-the-ballerina-bun-returns" target="_self">ballerina bun</a>. This effortless look is simple to achieve, looks cute and keeps your hair out of the way when you’re getting hot and bothered. <p> </p>
To get this look, create a really neat ballerina bun by using a hair doughnut. Begin by putting in roughly half a head of extensions and tying them into a ponytail high on your head. Next pull the ponytail through the doughnut before wrapping the ends over the doughnut so it can’t be traced. You can leave some hair out for a messy-chic look.<br>You can give this look a trendy update and wear a low bun instead. You can add accesries to the bun or give your look a twist and braid a small section from the middle or side all the way down to the bun.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-37_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-39_">2.	The relaxed side braid</span></h3><div title="Cute and Easy Summer Hairstyles" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-TBWPX ebxtzr pf-40_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/screenshot-20221017-140735_11zon-1666012187019_1200x.jpg?v=1666012186" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/screenshot-20221017-140735_11zon-1666012187019.jpg?v=1666012186 1536w" width="622" height="626" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" alt="Easy Summer Hairstyles" title="Cute and Easy Summer Hairstyles"/></div><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-41_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-43_">The relaxed side braid is another classic summer hairstyle. This is perfect for the heat as the braid goes over the shoulder, keeping the hair away your face and your back. If you’re heading out, opt for this pretty and girly look, which looks gorgeous with a slouchy summer dress or softening a more sporty or formal look.<br><br>You can create a really long braid which looks extra feminine and eye catching using human hair extensions Clip in all of your hair extensions before sweeping to the side and plaiting loosely. Pull out occasional strands to create a beachy vibe to the style, and finish with a shine spray to help your hair look vibrant and healthy.&nbsp;<br><br>If braiding is too difficult, perhaps try a <a href="https://www.cliphair.co.uk/blogs/hair-blog/5-killer-hairstyles-with-a-clip-in-ponytail-and-how-to-slay-them" target="_self">bubble</a> side ponytail instead for a stylish switch.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-cee5" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-jNHqnW kXSKNz pf-44_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-cqJhZP gRKDwp"><div class="sc-efQSVx kdrjec pf-45_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eySxxw fIKYYX pf-46_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-47_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-49_">3. Soft beachy waves</span></h3><div title="Summer Hairstyles" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-TBWPX ebxtzr pf-50_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/blob_11zon-1666011274932_1200x.jpg?v=1666011275" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/blob_11zon-1666011274932.jpg?v=1666011275 1536w" width="600" height="600" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" alt="Easy Summer Hairstyles" title="Summer Hairstyles"/></div><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-51_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-53_">Beachy waves are perhaps one of the most popular summer hairstyles. Thankfully, this is another look that is really easy to achieve. <p> </p>
You can use your straighteners to create this look. Simply put in your <a href="https://www.cliphair.co.uk/pages/clip-in-hair-extensions" target="_self">clip in hair extensions</a> and then, layer by layer, run your extensions down small sections of your hair in a wavy motion. This will create a soft wave. When you reach the top layer, use a fine-toothed comb to create some height and volume. Our double weft hair extensions are perfect for this look as they provide twice the amount of hair with the same amount of clips!
Finish off with a light mist of hairspray to hold the waves in place.
<br><br>Use soft, downward strokes to blend, but not rub, the dye into the hair in a way that is natural and soft. Avoid blocks of colour; you’re aiming for a subtle, sun kissed vibe. Think about which bits of your hair would naturally turn blonde if you spent a lot of time in the sun. The side mid lengths and the front should be your main focus.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-54_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-56_">4. The high ponytail </span></h3><div title="Summer Hairstyles" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-TBWPX ebxtzr pf-57_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-f9e8d35d--Summer-Hairstyles-high-pony_1200x.JPG?v=1591722762" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-f9e8d35d--Summer-Hairstyles-high-pony.JPG?v=1591722762 1536w" width="3072" height="3072" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" alt="Easy Summer Hairstyles" title="Summer Hairstyles"/></div><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-58_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-60_">An all-time, all season classic, the high ponytail is a timeless style that never disappoints. For summer, this super sleek look goes with just about anything, from a black maxi dress to an elegant two-piece. <p> </p>

Simply slick your own hair back into a ponytail, as high or low as your like and fix the extension ponytail on top of it! You can spice the look up a bit by adding some stunning hair accessories. Flick you ponytail for a <a href="https://www.cliphair.co.uk/blogs/hair-blog/spring-2020-hair-trends-top-hairstyles-cuts-and-colours-for-ss20" target="_self">super-fashionable</a> take on this classic.<p> </p>
You can try our 26″ hair extensions for a really striking long look. To get a high ponytail using human hair extensions, blow dry your natural hair straight before running your straighteners through your hair and extensions. Don’t forget to add serum to help achieve a mirror shine which looks stunning.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-61_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-63_">5. Balayage highlights</span></h3><div title="7 Cute and Easy Summer Hairstyles" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-TBWPX ebxtzr pf-64_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/screenshot-20221017-140735_11zon-1666012085245_1200x.jpg?v=1666012085" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/screenshot-20221017-140735_11zon-1666012085245.jpg?v=1666012085 1536w" width="616" height="622" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" alt="7 Cute and Easy Summer Hairstyles" title="7 Cute and Easy Summer Hairstyles"/></div><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-65_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-67_">If you’re not familiar with <a href="/blogs/hair-blog/how-to-balayage-and-root-drag-tutorial" target="_blank">balayage</a>, think of it as a more subtle version of ombre. The idea is the same – to get that sun kissed transition from dark to light – but the effect is more delicate and natural. This makes it a great option for girls who like to wear clip in hair extensions; the extra length gives hair the room it needs to create a seamless colour change.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-68_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-70_">6. The wavy bob</span></h3><div title="Summer Hairstyles" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-TBWPX ebxtzr pf-71_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-e68b55f4---easy-summer-hairstyles_1200x.JPG?v=1591722527" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-e68b55f4---easy-summer-hairstyles.JPG?v=1591722527 1536w" width="3072" height="3072" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" alt="Easy Summer Hairstyles" title="Summer Hairstyles"/></div><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-72_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-74_">If you are growing their tresses out, the wavy bob is great way to show your natural waves some love. The waves give your look a summer vibe while the bib gives it an edgy touch. </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-75_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-77_">7. Curls with bounce and body</span></h3><div title="DIY Balayage: " data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-TBWPX ebxtzr pf-78_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-7687e68b---2020-summer-hairstyles_1200x.JPG?v=1591722446" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-7687e68b---2020-summer-hairstyles.JPG?v=1591722446 1536w" width="3072" height="3072" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" alt="How to Balayage at Home" title="DIY Balayage: "/></div><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-79_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-81_">While straight hair is chic and fantastic, heat-based styling is pretty bad for the health of your hair. So, it’s a good idea to have at least a couple of days, every week, without it. To tease your own tresses into long and beautiful curls, blow dry and then attach your clip in extensions before you wind your hair into rollers. <p> </p>

